<br>
&quot;Well, it's a really complicated story,&quot; he began, sitting down in a chair.  &quot;You see, no one was alive during the First Dawn, and the story was told by the Goddess Ice to the First Elf Sukebeno.   You see, Ice had already been somewhat alive...she was the one that had kept Mahtim intact, during the Null...but I'll get to that.<br>
<br>
&quot;In the very beginning, there was the eternal Null.  The sun was too young to give the entire galaxy light, and everything was in darkness.  Mahtim was just a barren sphere, covered in ice, an unfertilized seed, if you will.  But suddenly, something happened.  The sun exploded!  It had grown so full of feeding on the darkness that it just erupted, and expanded instantly into the size we know it as today.  <br>
<br>
&quot;The magical radiance from the exploding star did something to the planet.  It kind of fertilized it, I guess.  But Ice had said the earth had shuddered beneath her, and suddenly there was life, and overwhelming heat.<br>
<br>
&quot;It was called the First Dawn.  The first Gods were then born.  Ice melted and was banished to the north and south poles, where she took form in the north.  Her aftermath created Sea.  Sea created Storm. Storm created Flower and Fire, and Wind.  The first six were born.<br>
<br>
&quot;But when Mahtim came alive, her seed was born.  In her very core, their was another Goddess.  She was born weak, and blind, because she was born in darkness and in the very womb of the earth.  But she was born in rage and hatred, because she was trapped within her womb, and could not escape.  Her name was Evil, the only Goddess that never witnessed the First Dawn.<br>
<br>
&quot;For thousands of years, the Gods went on creating without knowing her presence.  Ice knew, for she had shared the sphere with Evil before the Dawn.  But she said nothing, knowing she could not escape.<br>
<br>
&quot;And then Evil became stronger.  She fed off of Mahtim's life and spawned her own creatures, which were born form foul places and terrorized the surface. When Humans were created, the Last Race created, Evil found a new way to make her presence known.<br>
<br>
&quot;She came to the Princess Sanya of Osiria, the Second Kingdom, in the form of a great sorceress, for she is the Queen of Sorcery.  She tricked the girl into killing her brother, who was the lover of Princess Katarina, the heir to the Dratilian throne and the Keeper of The Falcon.  She knew that if she held this Heart Of Dragons, as it was often called, in her possession, she could summon Maiem, the First Mother Dragon, and her children, and have them do her bidding.  But KAtarina killed Sanya and then herself, and the Heart was lost forever.<br>
<br>
&quot;We're still trying to find it.  If we get to it before Evil does, we can stop her form destroying MAhitm.  Right now, the Goddess lives in the shell of Sorceress Artema.  She is extremely powerful, but if she were ever to surface from her prison, the world would be doomed.  Her brethren are no longer here, because they died long ago.  Without them, she cannot be controlled, if she were ever to surface and obtain the Token.&quot;<br>
<br>
Cedric took a deep breath.  &quot;Well, that's it in a nutshell.  Any questions?&quot;<br>
